President Obama called President Goodluck Jonathan of Nigeria to congratulate him on his election victory. He commended the people of Nigeria for their resolve and patience during the elections. The success of the elections was credited to Nigerian voters who waited in long lines and watched their votes being counted. The Independent National Electoral Commission, the National Youth Service Corps, and Nigeria's civil society were also acknowledged for their role in ensuring a fair process. However, the post-election violence that occurred was condemned, and it was emphasized that violence has no place in a democratic society. The statement called on Nigeria's leaders and people to come together and build a future that addresses the aspirations of all Nigerians. Nigeria was encouraged to become a model for Africa by showing what is possible when people from different parties, ethnicities, and faith backgrounds work together for peace and prosperity. President Obama expressed his commitment to strengthening the partnership between the United States and Nigeria.